7f076-8 | 2026-06-12T11:52:09Z | session:7f076ca6-6975-44ae-9848-d41832e499f0 | Assistant: OK, definitive answer from OpenRouter's own OpenAPI spec (`/openapi.json` at `components.schemas.STTResponse`): \n  \n ```json \n { \n   "description": "STT response containing transcribed text and optional usage statistics", \n   "properties": { \n     "text":  { "description": "The transcribed text", "type": "string" }, \n     "usage": { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/STTUsage" } \n   }, \n   "required": ["text"] \n } \n ``` \n  \n And the request schema (`STTRequest`) has no `response_format` or `timestamp_granularities` field — only `model`, `input_audio` (base64 + format), `language`, `temperature`, and a `provider` passthrough. \n  \n **OpenRouter strips segments at the gateway.** Even though `whisper-large-v3-turbo` runs on Groq (which natively supports `verbose_json` with segments) and OpenAI's Whisper API supports them too, OpenRouter's response envelope flattens to text-only. \n  \n So the choice is real: \n  \n - **All 6 OpenRouter STT models work**, but produce text-only transcripts. \n - **Text-only transcripts kill AIChapterCompiler** — every line stamps at 0s, so the LLM has nothing to anchor chapter starts to. Chapters and ads can't be inferred. \n - **ElevenLabs Scribe** returns segments. **Apple on-device** returns segments. Either provides the timestamps AIChapterCompiler needs.
