to `Definition` paragraphs only. \n 3. **`audit` does not pass contested-claim state into the prompt** (`WikiPrompts.swift:142-162`). Brief §7 mandates the regen must "remove, reduce confidence, or surface counter-citation." Current prompt only sees the title + chunk set. \n 4. **Citation peek wiring is a `Notification.Name` posting**, not a typed deep link (work-report §UI). Outside the strict pipeline scope but worth noting — silent if no observer. \n  \n ## Silent failure modes \n  \n 1. **Triggers never fire.** `wikiAutoGenerateOnTranscriptIngest` reads as `false` default and has no observer; even if flipped, no event source exists. The auto-refresh contract from brief §9.4 is unreachable. Highest-impact silent no-op in the pipeline. \n 2. **Missing API key on auto-trigger path.** `WikiOpenRouterClient.compileLive` (`:113-120`) throws `missingCredential`. The user-invoked sheet surfaces this (`WikiGenerateSheet.swift:274-277`); a hypothetical background path has nowhere to display it. \n 3. **Empty RAG result → empty page persisted.** `WikiPrompts.renderChunks` falls back to "no evidence available — return empty sections" (`:168-169`); the model dutifully returns empty sections; verifier keeps them; storage writes a hollow page with `confidence=0.5` (parser default, `WikiResponseParser.swift:35`). \n 4. **`WikiResponseParser` swallows malformed claims/citations.** Field-level `compactMap` (`:67`, `:84`) drops bad rows without surfacing a warning. A response with 10 broken citations becomes a confidently-empty page. \n 5. **`UUID(uuidString:)` requirement** (`WikiResponseParser.swift:97`). If the LLM emits a non-UUID `episode_id` (or omits it), citation is silently dropped and the claim may then be dropped by the verifier — no "model hallucinated an ID" telemetry. \n 6. **`CostLedger.log` is fire-and-forget** (`WikiOpenRouterClient.swift:193-203`). Usage decoding failures eat silently (`try?`). \n 7. **Verifier preserves empty section with `editorialNote`** (`WikiVerifier.swift:66-68`) — set but `WikiSection.hasContent` returns `false` and the renderer drops it, so the note never appears to the user. \n  \n ## Biggest gaps (user-visible impact, ranked) \n  \n 1. **No auto-refresh.** Pages only exist when the user manually compiles via `WikiGenerateSheet`. The brief's "every new episode triggers a partial regen" (§9.4) and the deep dive's whole "automatic, not user-invoked" thesis (§7) are unbuilt. `WikiTriggers` is a dead library. \n 2. **No per-episode extraction fan-out.** `extractedTopics`/`extractedPeople` plumbing exists in the trigger enum but nothing produces them — the "topic discovery as you listen" loop is closed off. \n 3. **No regen diff / no contested-claim feedback loop.** Brief §5 "Wrong button" and §7 "Show diff" both unbuilt; user has no way to mark a claim as wrong and see the next compile address it. \n 4. **Verifier's 60% fuzzy band launders paraphrase as medium-confidence.** A model that hallucinates plausibly-similar wording will earn a `.medium` rule rather than a `.low` or drop. Erodes the provenance contract. \n 5. **Empty-evidence compiles still persist a low-quality skeleton.** Combined with no retry, a user typing a query with no RAG hits gets a confidently-empty page they can't tell apart from a real one. \n  \n Assistant: Agent 1 (pipeline) landed. The headline is brutal: **`WikiTriggers.swift` is a dead library — no caller anywhere in `App/`**. The `wikiAutoGenerateOnTranscriptIngest` setting is read by nothing. The brief's "every new episode triggers a partial regen" thesis is entirely unbuilt; pages exist only when the user manually taps Generate. \n  \n Other major findings: \n - **No per-episode extraction fan-out** (`extract_topics`/`extract_entities`/`extract_quotes`/`link_to_existing_pages` — the deep dive's whole "topic discovery as you listen" loop). The trigger enum *consumes* these events but nothing produces them. \n - **Verifier's 60% token-overlap → `.medium`** (`WikiVerifier.swift:209`) silently launders paraphrase as medium-confidence. Brief demands verbatim substring. \n - **`general_knowledge` accepted in any section** instead of just `Definition` (`WikiVerifier.swift:102` vs brief §9.1). \n - **No retry / partial-section recovery** — single `do/catch` in the generate sheet. \n - **Empty-RAG → confidently-empty page persisted** (`WikiPrompts.swift:168` falls back to "no evidence available", model returns empty sections, verifier keeps them, storage writes a hollow `confidence=0.5` page indistinguishable from a real one). \n - **No Markdown export to iCloud Drive** (deep-dive §7 — `WikiStorage` is JSON-only). \n - **No "Show diff" on regenerate**, no contested-claim feedback loop. [...] - `TranscriptIngestService.persistAndIndex` now fires a fire-and-forget wiki refresh after AI-chapter compile, gated on `wikiAutoGenerateOnTranscriptIngest`. Topics seeded from the episode title + chapter titles (zero-op on fresh installs with no compiled pages)
