0f3f2-35 | 2026-06-12T12:05:48Z | session:0f3f24f7-54de-49f8-b160-a92f735f6a00 | APPROACH: Added a `SummarySource` enum field to `EpisodeSummary` (the preferred struct-field approach). \n  \n - The enum has three cases: `.llm`, `.publisherDescription`, `.unavailable`. \n - The `source` parameter defaults to `.llm` in the initializer, so no existing call-sites without an explicit `source` argument silently break — but every call-site in the adapter is now explicit. \n - The `parseSummary` LLM path tags results `.llm`. The empty-transcript guard and the no-API-key guard both tag results `.publisherDescription`. The episode-not-found guard tags `.unavailable`. \n - The tool result serializer in `AgentTools+Podcast.swift` now includes `"summary_source"` in the JSON payload using `summary.source.rawValue`. \n  \n FILES CHANGED: \n - `/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Agent/PodcastAgentToolValues.swift` — added `SummarySource` enum and `source` field to `EpisodeSummary` \n - `/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Agent/LiveEpisodeSummarizerAdapter.swift` — all four return sites tagged with explicit `.unavailable`, `.publisherDescription`, or `.llm` \n - `/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Agent/AgentTools+Podcast.swift` — added `"summary_source": summary.source.rawValue` to the tool result payload \n  \n EXAMPLE TOOL RESULT JSON FOR A FALLBACK CASE (no API key, episode found): \n ```json \n { \n   "episode_id": "3FA85F64-5717-4562-B3FC-2C963F66AFA6", \n   "summary": "In this episode we talk with experts about ...", \n   "summary_source": "publisherDescription" \n } \n ``` \n  \n The LLM now sees `"summary_source": "publisherDescription"` and can communicate to the user that the text is the publisher blurb rather than an AI-generated summary. The UI code does not need to change — it can continue rendering `summary.summary` regardless of source. \n 
