d0e67-2 | 2026-06-12T12:15:35Z | session:d0e6775b-4ac9-4467-b961-7e78de0f61eb | **Data model** \n - `Episode.triageDecision: TriageDecision?` (`.inbox` | `.archived`) + `triageRationale: String?`, backward-compatible Codable. \n - `App/Sources/Podcast/Episode+Triage.swift` for the enum + convenience accessors. [...] ## Blockers \n 1. **🔴 Critical: triage state wiped on every feed refresh.** `AppStateStore+Episodes.swift:82-96` preserves `playbackPosition`/`played`/etc. on RSS merge but NOT `triageDecision`/`triageRationale`. Every refresh resets archive decisions. The LLM redoes the work and decisions flicker. \n 2. **🔴 Notifications/auto-downloads fire before triage runs.** Triage is the *last* step in `refreshAll`, so a soon-to-be-archived episode already pushed a notification, queued a download, and surfaced in Continue Listening. Violates "silently archived." [...] ANALYSIS: The merge block of `upsertEpisodes` was clobbering `triageDecision`, `triageRationale`, and (added by agent C since the brief was written) `triageIsHero` on every feed refresh. The refresh pipeline also fired side effects synchronously inside the upsert sweep, before any triage verdict existed. I confirmed `triageIsHero` exists on `Episode.swift` and added it to the merge alongside the two fields the brief named. I chose the polling approach over a one-cycle-tolerance approach because `InboxTriageService.isRunning` is already `private(set)` (observable without modifying agent C's file), the wait is bounded to 60s, and the correctness win outweighs the modest latency to pull-to-refresh. \n  \n ACTIONS: \n - `App/Sources/State/AppStateStore+Episodes.swift`: added three merge-preservation lines. \n - `App/Sources/Services/SubscriptionRefreshService.swift`: changed `upsertEpisodes` call site to `evaluateAutoDownload: false`; refactored `apply` to return a `PendingSideEffects` struct; collect per-feed pending effects through the sweep; kick triage and poll `InboxTriageService.shared.isRunning` until false (with 60s deadline); then dispatch surviving (`!isTriageArchived`) IDs through a new `dispatchSideEffects` that calls `EpisodeDownloadService.evaluateAutoDownload`, `TranscriptIngestService.evaluateAutoIngest`, and `NotificationService.notifyNewEpisodes`. Applied the same gate to the single-podcast `refresh(_:store:)` path. \n - `App/Resources/whats-new.json`: added a 19:02 entry describing the user-facing improvement. \n  \n RESULTS: \n - Blocker 1 merge-preservation lines added at `AppStateStore+Episodes.swift:91–96`: \n ```swift \n // Preserve the AI Inbox triage verdict across feed refreshes; \n // without this, an archived episode reappears on the next \n // refresh and the LLM redoes the classification. \n merged.triageDecision = prior.triageDecision \n merged.triageRationale = prior.triageRationale \n merged.triageIsHero = prior.triageIsHero \n ```
