f3b46-2 | 2026-06-12T12:38:17Z | session:f3b466c6-7791-44b3-b004-aae2066a9019 | - Three async UniFFI exports on `PodcastrCore` (`#[uniffi::export(async_runtime = "tokio")]`): \n   - `nip46_start_nostrconnect(relay_url, app_name, app_url?, app_image?) -> String` — generates session key + secret, builds URI, ensures relay is in pool, stashes `PendingNip46` on `Inner`, returns URI. \n   - `nip46_await_signer(timeout_secs) -> String` — consumes pending state, runs `BunkerSigner::await_inbound`, calls `client.set_signer(signer).await` directly (skipping `NostrRuntime::set_signer`'s `block_on` per the advisor's note), updates session via `login_pubkey`, fires `SignerConnected { pubkey }`, returns pubkey hex. \n   - `nip46_disconnect()` — clears pending state, calls `session.logout()`, calls `client.unset_signer().await`, fires `SignerDisconnected { reason }`. \n  \n **Key design choices and trade-offs:** \n - **Did NOT use `nostr_sdk::NostrConnect`** — it lives in the separate `nostr-connect` 0.44 crate, which is not in our Cargo.toml (and the task forbade editing Cargo.toml). The `nostr-sdk` 0.44.1 prelude does not re-export it. So I ported highlighter's hand-rolled `BunkerSigner` on top of `nostr::nips::nip46::*` primitives. Documented in nip46.rs module doc. \n - **Two-call pattern** (`start` then `await`) per spec — `start` synchronously returns URI for QR display, `await` blocks for pairing. State carried via `PendingNip46` in `Inner` (take-once semantics so a stray second `await` fails cleanly with a clear error). \n - **`block_on` avoidance** — `nip46_await_signer` calls `client.set_signer(signer).await` directly, not `runtime().set_signer()` (which uses `block_on`). This matches highlighter's pattern and the advisor's warning. Same-runtime panic avoided. [...] - `nip46_uri::build_nostr_connect_uri` — builds `nostrconnect://<pubkey>?metadata=…&relay=…&secret=…`. Hand-rolled because the SDK's `NostrConnectURI::Display` for the Client variant doesn't include `secret=`. \n - `nip46_uri::random_secret` — 16 bytes → 32 hex chars from `secp256k1::rand::OsRng` (re-exported via `nostr_sdk::prelude`, so no new dep). [...] - `bunker://` paste flow (URI-from-signer) — only `nostrconnect://` is implemented per spec. \n - `auth_url` browser challenge plumbing.
