c1691-49 | 2026-06-12T13:56:41Z | session:c1691db0-d63e-4062-adad-1cfa0d679d09 | **0.1 — No `catch_unwind` on FFI entry points that `block_on` network/LLM futures.** *(crash class)* \n The crate has **zero** `catch_unwind`, builds as `cdylib`, and has no `panic = "abort"`. Actor-path panics are caught upstream by nmp_core — but the *direct* `extern "C"` entries (`ffi/chat_complete.rs:179`, `provider_complete.rs`, `provider_embeddings`, `perplexity_search`, `elevenlabs_scribe`, `openrouter_whisper`, `byok_auth.rs:40`, plus the JNI entries in `android.rs`) drive futures via `runtime.block_on(...)` with no guard. A panic in any of those futures (a downstream `.unwrap()`, a parser overflow, a reqwest/serde edge) unwinds across the C ABI → UB/abort, crashing the shell. \n **Fix:** one shared `ffi_guard<T>(fallback, f)` helper wrapping each entry, returning the file's existing degrade value (null / `{"error":"panic"}`) on catch. **Effort M, risk low, payoff high.** Also worth pairing with `[profile.release] panic = "abort"` so even an unguarded path is a *defined* abort, not UB. \n  \n **0.2 — Required float projection fields can serialize to `null` → dropped frame.** *(matches the exact bug class that started this whole session)* \n `serde_json` emits `NaN`/`Inf` as `null`; a Swift non-optional `Double` then throws → **entire frame dropped**. Several required, non-`Option` floats have no finite-guard at source: `projections/clips.rs:29,32`, `projections/library.rs:227,268` (`start_secs`), `agent.rs:137` (`pick_score`), `inbox.rs:20` (`priority_score`), `knowledge.rs:36`, `download.rs:62` (`progress`). Only `WidgetSnapshot.position_fraction` is guarded today (`snapshot_widget.rs:129`). \n **Fix:** a `#[serde(serialize_with = "finite_or_zero")]` on each required float (centralized, regression-proof). **Effort S–M, risk low, payoff medium-high.** \n  [...] 1. **The concrete, remotely-triggerable frame-drop:** `parse_duration` accepts the *strings* `"NaN"`/`"inf"` (Rust's `f64::from_str` does). A hostile/buggy feed `<itunes:duration>NaN</itunes:duration>` → `Some(NaN)` → `build_stub_chapters` `step = NaN` → required `ChapterSummary.start_secs = NaN` → JSON `null` → Swift throws → **whole frame dropped, from any RSS feed.** This is the bug that justifies 0.2 at all. Fix at the inlet: `.ok().filter(|v| v.is_finite())`. \n 2. **The `.generated.swift` bridge files are hand-maintained** (the header literally says so) — the misleading "generated" name *invites* the stale-mirror divergence behind #371. Landing the codegen or renaming the files is higher-leverage than any single contract test. \n 3. `clamp()` doesn't sanitize `NaN` (`picks_module.rs:218`, `knowledge.rs:269,408`) — reads as a guard, isn't one. A `finite_or(default)` helper would encode actual intent. \n  \n ## Fable's corrected priority order
