rollo-86 | 2026-06-12T14:02:55Z | session:rollout-2026-05-11T08-21-02-019e157b-4b15-77a0-8003-a3ae75cf8c26 | - **P1: Background downloads are configured but the app delegate handoff is missing.** `EpisodeDownloadService` creates a background `URLSession` with launch events, but `AppDelegate` has no `application(_:handleEventsForBackgroundURLSession:completionHandler:)` path and the download delegate has no completion-handler drain. That can leave background-completed downloads stale until foregrounding. See [EpisodeDownloadService.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Services/EpisodeDownloadService.swift:39), [EpisodeDownloadService.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Services/EpisodeDownloadService.swift:99), [AppDelegate.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/App/AppDelegate.swift:21), [EpisodeDownloadService+Delegate.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Services/EpisodeDownloadService+Delegate.swift:50).
rollo-87 | 2026-06-12T14:02:55Z | session:rollout-2026-05-11T08-21-02-019e157b-4b15-77a0-8003-a3ae75cf8c26 | - **P1: “Queued” downloads are modeled in UI/state but not actually produced.** The service transitions directly to `.downloading`, and Wi-Fi-only auto-downloads just log and return when Wi-Fi is unavailable. Meanwhile Settings, episode detail, and swipe actions expose queued behavior. See [DownloadState.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Podcast/DownloadState.swift:10), [EpisodeDownloadService.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Services/EpisodeDownloadService.swift:138), [EpisodeDownloadService.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Services/EpisodeDownloadService.swift:217), [DownloadsManagerView.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Features/Settings/DownloadsManagerView.swift:184).
rollo-88 | 2026-06-12T14:02:55Z | session:rollout-2026-05-11T08-21-02-019e157b-4b15-77a0-8003-a3ae75cf8c26 | - **P2: Offline/downloaded state can lie if the local file disappears.** The download store can check existence, but Downloads, Settings, and projections trust persisted `.downloaded`; playback falls back to streaming if the file is missing. Offline users can tap a “downloaded” episode and hit a network failure. See [EpisodeDownloadStore.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Podcast/EpisodeDownloadStore.swift:79), [AudioEngine.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Audio/AudioEngine.swift:155), [DownloadsManagerView.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Features/Settings/DownloadsManagerView.swift:184), [AppStateStore+EpisodeProjections.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/State/AppStateStore+EpisodeProjections.swift:91).
rollo-89 | 2026-06-12T14:02:55Z | session:rollout-2026-05-11T08-21-02-019e157b-4b15-77a0-8003-a3ae75cf8c26 | - **P3: “Latest N” sounds like a retention cap, but only selects from newly inserted episodes.** The policy says older items may auto-prune, yet the service only downloads the newest N from the current refresh batch and never prunes older downloads. See [AutoDownloadPolicy.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Podcast/AutoDownloadPolicy.swift:12), [EpisodeDownloadService.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Services/EpisodeDownloadService.swift:223), [ShowDetailView.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Features/Library/ShowDetailView.swift:385).
rollo-90 | 2026-06-12T14:02:58Z | session:rollout-2026-05-11T08-21-02-019e157b-4b15-77a0-8003-a3ae75cf8c26 | - **P2: OPML import “background” copy overstates durability.** The import task continues after dismissing the sheet, but fetched feeds are held in memory and committed only after the whole loop completes. Killing the app mid-import loses successful work. See [OPMLImportSheet.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Features/Library/OPMLImportSheet.swift:176), [OPMLImportSheet.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Features/Library/OPMLImportSheet.swift:214), [OPMLImportSheet.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Features/Library/OPMLImportSheet.swift:351), [OPMLImportSheet.swift](/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Features/Library/OPMLImportSheet.swift:383).
