c1691-59 | 2026-06-12T14:06:03Z | session:c1691db0-d63e-4062-adad-1cfa0d679d09 | Done. The PR is open and correct: base `master`, 7 files, +461/-7. \n  \n ## Summary \n  \n **PR URL: https://github.com/pablof7z/nostr-multi-platform/pull/1068** (open, base `master`) \n  \n ### Chosen design + why \n Opt-in **per-projection change-gating** via a `ChangeGate` trait + a new `register_gated` registry method, keeping the existing `register` as always-run. \n  \n - `ChangeGate { fn current(&self) -> u64 }`, implemented for `AtomicU64` — so an `Arc<AtomicU64>` rev counter (which the consuming app already maintains) is the natural gate, exactly as the brief recommended. This was cleaner than a bespoke `dyn ChangeGate`-only design because it makes the canonical case (an atomic rev) zero-ceremony while still allowing custom gates. \n - Per-key memo is **interior-mutable** (`Mutex<Option<(u64, Value)>>` on each `ProjectionEntry`), because `run(&self)` is driven from `make_update` through a shared `&self` path. This avoids rippling `&mut` through the whole emit path. The closure runs **outside** the memo lock, so a slow/panicking closure never holds it, and `catch_unwind` panic isolation (D6) is preserved for both gated and ungated entries. \n - Ungated `register` is byte-for-byte behavior-preserving (no gate ⇒ never touches the memo). \n  \n ### Files changed (7) \n - `crates/nmp-core/src/kernel/snapshot_registry.rs` — `ChangeGate` trait + impl, `ProjectionEntry`, `register_gated`, gated `run()`. \n - `crates/nmp-core/src/kernel/snapshot_registry_tests.rs` — 4 new tests. \n - `crates/nmp-core/src/kernel/mod.rs` + `crates/nmp-core/src/lib.rs` — re-export `ChangeGate` (public + `__ffi_internal`). \n - `crates/nmp-core/src/substrate/app_host.rs` — `AppHost::register_snapshot_projection_gated`. \n - `crates/nmp-ffi/src/lib.rs` — `NmpApp::register_snapshot_projection_gated` (inherent + trait impl). \n - `crates/nmp-app-template/src/builder.rs` — `NmpAppBuilder` impl. \n  \n ### New 