rollo-137 | 2026-06-12T14:13:37Z | session:rollout-2026-05-13T09-40-04-019e2010-60db-72b0-af0f-d40f44ca1989 | Assistant: {"findings":[{"title":"[P1] Avoid full feed adoption before external playback","body":"When `feed_url` is supplied, this awaits `resolveExternalPodcastID`, which calls `SubscriptionService.ensurePodcast` before playback; that helper performs a network RSS fetch and upserts every parsed episode. In the normal `search_podcast_directory` → `play_external_episode` flow, a one-off play can therefore hang behind a slow feed request and then add the show's whole backlog to Home/Library even though the user did not subscribe. Start playback with an existing/Unknown podcast ID and hydrate only podcast metadata asynchronously.","confidence_score":0.88,"priority":1,"code_location":{"absolute_file_path":"/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Agent/LivePodcastAgentToolDeps.swift","line_range":{"start":213,"end":213}}},{"title":"[P1] Check subscriptions before reporting already subscribed","body":"After the split, `store.podcast(feedURL:)` means the app merely knows the feed, not that the user follows it. If an external play has already created a `Podcast` row, `subscribe_podcast` returns `already_subscribed: true` here and never creates a `PodcastSubscription`, so the agent's follow/download-and-transcribe path silently leaves the show unsubscribed. Resolve the podcast first, then check `store.subscription(podcastID:)` or call `SubscriptionService.addSubscription`.","confidence_score":0.94,"priority":1,"code_location":{"absolute_file_path":"/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Agent/LivePodcastDirectoryAdapter.swift","line_range":{"start":120,"end":120}}},{"title":"[P2] Use follow state for Discover subscribe checks","body":"This has the same known-versus-followed problem in the UI: a podcast row created by external playback makes search results show the disabled checkmark because `store.podcast(feedURL:)` is non-nil, even though no `PodcastSubscription` exists. Users then cannot subscribe from Discover; the check should be based on `store.subscription(podcastID:)` after resolving the feed.","confidence_score":0.92,"priority":2,"code_location":{"absolute_file_path":"/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Features/Library/DiscoverSearchForm.swift","line_range":{"start":268,"end":270}}},{"title":"[P2] Don't skip OPML rows for known-but-unfollowed podcasts","body":"`fetchForAdoption` now drops any OPML row whose feed is merely present in `state.podcasts`. Known-but-unfollowed feeds are expected after `ensurePodcast`/external play, so importing an OPML that contains that show counts it as skipped and never adds the follow row. The duplicate check needs to be against `state.subscriptions`, not all known podcasts.","confidence_score":0.9,"priority":2,"code_location":{"absolute_file_path":"/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Services/SubscriptionService.swift","line_range":{"start":160,"end":162}}},{"title":"[P1] Keep the test target compiling after the model split","body":"The app target builds, but the scheme's test target still has many fixtures using the old `Episode(subscriptionID:)` initializer, so `xcodebuild ... build-for-testing` fails immediately after this signature change. Migrate those tests/helpers to `podcastID` or keep a compatibility initializer before landing the refactor.","confidence_score":0.86,"priority":1,"code_location":{"absolute_file_path":"/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/App/Sources/Podcast/Episode.swift","line_range":{"start":86,"end":89}}}],"overall_correctness":"patch is incorrect","overall_explanation":"The patch breaks important subscribe/import flows by treating known podcasts as followed, and the external-play path now blocks on and ingests whole feeds. The test target also no longer compiles after the model split.","overall_confidence_score":0.9}
