tor for \n // N sequential Blossom uploads (D8)... \n let episodes_queued = episode_ids_to_backfill.len(); \n let mut episodes_accepted = 0usize; \n for episode_id in episode_ids_to_backfill { \n     let body = serde_json::json!({ "op": "publish_episode", "episode_id": episode_id }); \n     if self_dispatch_publish(handler.app, body) { \n         episodes_accepted += 1; \n     } \n } \n ``` \n  \n New helper `self_dispatch_publish` in `nmp_dispatch.rs` wraps `nmp_app_dispatch_action` for the `podcast.publish` namespace (returns immediately, never blocks). The dispatched `{"op":"publish_episode","episode_id":...}` is the same action the old Swift loop fired via `kernelPublishEpisode` — each lands in its own actor tick. Response carries `episodes_queued` (policy decision, D0-owned) and `episodes_accepted` (FFI accepts). \n  \n ### Preserved \n Flip detection, D0 kernel ownership, show republish, reuse of the `publish_episode` path. `publish_episode` reverted to `fn` (private) since it's reached via dispatch again. Swift side still just triggers `update_owned` (comment updated to note self-enqueue/D8). \n  \n ### Test \n Adapted to assert the enqueue contract: \n ``` \n test private_to_public_flip_backfills_all_episodes_as_kind54 ... ok   (episodes_queued == 3, episodes_accepted == 0 under null app) \n test already_public_show_update_does_not_backfill_episodes ... ok      (episodes_queued == 0) \n ``` \n Full crate: `1202 passed; 0 failed`. The live-kernel fan-out is covered by the existing headless `nipf4_publish` scenario path.
