c1691-151 | 2026-06-12T22:03:08Z | session:c1691db0-d63e-4062-adad-1cfa0d679d09 |  \n ### Destination change (before → after) \n  \n **Before** (hardcoded in `run_tests.sh`): \n ``` \n -destination "platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17,OS=latest" \n ``` \n  \n **After** (runtime discovery, `/Users/pablofernandez/Work/podcast-player/.worktrees/ci-sim-destination/ci_scripts/run_tests.sh`): \n ```bash \n if [ -z "${TEST_DESTINATION:-}" ]; then \n   available="$(xcrun simctl list devices available)" \n   # 1. prefer a simulator named "* ci" (the runner's purpose-built sim) \n   udid="$(printf '%s\n' "$available" | sed -n 's/.* ci (\([0-9A-F-]\{36\}\)) .*/\1/p' | head -1)" \n   # 2. fall back to any available iPhone simulator \n   if [ -z "$udid" ]; then \n     udid="$(printf '%s\n' "$available" | sed -n 's/^ *iPhone[^(]*(\([0-9A-F-]\{36\}\)) .*/\1/p' | head -1)" \n   fi \n   # 3. loud failure if nothing found \n   if [ -z "$udid" ]; then \n     echo "error: no available iPhone simulator on this runner" >&2; xcrun simctl list devices available >&2; exit 70 \n   fi \n   TEST_DESTINATION="platform=iOS Simulator,id=$udid" \n fi \n ``` \n  \n The destination is now passed by UDID (`platform=iOS Simulator,id=<udid>`) rather than by name, which is more robust. `-skipPackagePluginValidation` and the rest of the xcodebuild invocation are unchanged.
