c1691-193 | 2026-06-13T00:26:54Z | session:c1691db0-d63e-4062-adad-1cfa0d679d09 | ## Item 1 (HEADLINE) — Domain sub-projections as per-domain typed sidecars + per-domain revs \n  \n **What/why:** Replace "one global rev → full-library re-serialize + full-frame decode on any change" with per-domain push deltas. A `PersistPosition` tick (~1/30s) or download-progress report then ships ~1KB of playback/downloads JSON instead of triggering a multi-MB pull+decode. This is the 10x-scale fix the wiki explicitly calls for, and it deletes the four accreted mitigations' root cause. \n **Wiki:** `docs/wiki/change-gate-projections.md` ("Domain Revision Tracking", "Domain Sub-Projections"), `kernel-snapshot-emission.md`, `android-snapshot-push.md`, `reactive-update-model.md`. \n **Scope: L**, staged as 4 independently-landable PRs: \n  \n - **PR-1 (S, ship day 1):** Delete the dead `register_snapshot_projection_gated("podcast.snapshot", …)` block in `apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/ffi/register.rs`. Zero consumer risk (verified above); immediate actor-thread CPU win. Pull path untouched. \n - **PR-2 (M-L, the long pole, Rust-only):** Per-domain revs + producers. \n   - `src/state/mod.rs`: `Infra` currently carries ONE global `rev: Arc<AtomicU64>` cloned into all 15 substates. Add a per-domain rev (e.g. `DomainRevs` struct or a `domain_rev` field per substate-scoped `Infra`); substate `bump()` bumps domain + global (global stays for pull-path compatibility). \n   - Domain set (first cut): `podcast.library` (library+categories — the big one), `podcast.playback` (now_playing+queue), `podcast.downloads`, `podcast.inbox`, `podcast.settings`, `podcast.identity`, `podcast.widget`, and a `podcast.misc` catch-all (wiki/picks/clips/transcripts/social/agent/discovery/voice/publish/tasks — small payloads, gate on global rev initially). The per-domain serializers largely already exist as `src/ffi/snapshot_library.rs`, `snapshot_queue.rs`, `snapshot_downloads.rs`, `snapshot_settings.rs`, `snapshot_identity.rs`, `snapshot_widget.rs`, `snapshot_categories.rs` — re-aim them at per-domain envelopes (each carrying its domain rev for shell stale-drop). \n   - Register via `register_typed_snapshot_projection`: closure holds `last_emitted: AtomicU64`; unchanged domain rev → `None` (omitted from frame); changed → JSON bytes in `TypedProjectionData{schema_id: "podcast.library", version: 1}`. \n   - Extend `nmp_app_podcast_decode_update_frame` (`src/ffi/snapshot.rs`) to decode all `podcast.*` sidecars into `v.projections[key]` — clone of the signed_events pattern. \n   - **Tests (non-negotiable, per the #371/#384 lesson):** Rust frame round-trip fixtures per domain + "playback tick frame excludes library" assertion + Swift `KernelDecoding` fixture tests fed by Rust-emitted JSON (snake_case contract — no explicit CodingKeys in embedded types). \n - **PR-3 (M, Swift):** `App/Sources/Bridge/KernelBridge+Callbacks.swift`, `KernelModel.swift`, `KernelDecoding.swift`, `AppStateStore+KernelProjection.swift` — apply per-domain payloads present in the frame instead of triggering `pullPodcastSnapshotIfChanged`; keep pull as cold-start hydration + fallback when a frame carries no podcast keys (staged cutover, never a flag-day). Keep widget/Live-Activity feeds (`applyNowPlayingSnapshot`) wired to the playback domain. \n - **PR-4 (S-M, Android):** `src/android.rs` JNI already returns the decoded JSON envelope, so Kotlin gets the keys for free; update `android/.../KernelBridge.kt` + `PodcastSnapshot.kt` to apply per-domain frames, same pull fallback. \n  \n **Validation (Haiku-verifiable):** yes. `NMP_PERF rust_update … payload_bytes=` log line already exists — build_run_sim with a populated library, play an episode 2 min, assert payload_bytes on playback ticks drops from ~MBs to ~KBs and UI position still advances; screenshot player + library. Android same via adb logcat. Plus cargo + headless harness. [...] The prompt's premise — "split `podcast.snapshot` into per-domain keys via `register_snapshot_projection_gated`" — is **architecturally wrong for NMP v0.5.0**, and I verified why at the source: \n  \n 1. **Generic JSON projections never reach the wire anymore.** Since ADR-0044/PR-B (nmp v0.3.0), `encode_snapshot_with_envelope` (`/Users/pablofernandez/Work/nostr-multi-platform/crates/nmp-core/src/update_envelope/tier3_frame.rs:39`) encodes ONLY the typed Tier-3 envelope + the `typed_projections` FlatBuffer sidecar. The `KernelSnapshot::projections` map (where `register_snapshot_projection_gated` output lands) is built every emit and then **discarded by the encoder**. \n 2. **Consequence: the gated `"podcast.snapshot"` registration in `register.rs:~355` is pure actor-thread waste today.** On every rev-changed emit it does `serde_json::from_str` of the multi-MB payload (output thrown away); on every rev-unchanged emit the registry memo does a deep `Value::clone()` of the cached multi-MB tree (`snapshot_registry.rs` `value_for_tick`) — also thrown away. I verified every real consumer (iOS `KernelModel.pullPodcastSnapshotIfChanged`, Android `android.rs:383`, headless harness, TUI) uses the **pull** symbol `nmp_app_podcast_snapshot`, not the registered projection. The shell's actual data path is: push frame (no podcast payload) → notification → rev-gated pull of the full monolithic JSON → full `PodcastUpdate` decode. \n 3. **The correct v0.5.0-native seam already exists, no nmp-core change needed:** `NmpApp::register_typed_snapshot_projection(key, || Option<TypedProjectionData>)` (`crates/nmp-ffi/src/snapshot.rs:48`). Returning `None` **omits the key from the frame entirely that tick** — true per-domain delta frames, strictly better than the #1068 JSON gate (which still clones+ships unchanged keys). The app already has the exact consumer pattern: `decode_signed_events_sidecar` → inject under `v.projections[key]` (`apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/ffi/snapshot.rs`, PR #385). So the answer to "does #1068's gate suffice?" is: **it's moot — use typed sidecars with Option-gating; per-domain revs are app-local; zero upstream changes.** [...] The per-domain frame work is **not just a perf win — the push pipeline is currently dead on BOTH shells**, and on Android it's actively *harmful*: \n  \n - **iOS:** `KernelBridge.decode(pointer:)` (`App/Sources/Bridge/KernelBridge.swift:234-256`) still requires `v.projections["podcast.snapshot"]`. Since NMP v0.3.0 typed-first the generic projections map is never encoded, and #396 deleted that registration. **Every push frame fails decode** ("snapshot frame missing podcast.snapshot projection") and `sink.handler` never fires. iOS today is 100% pull-driven: report-channel hooks + `pullPodcastSnapshotIfChanged` (full multi-MB Rust serialize + full off-main decode per change). Background rev bumps (triage completion, async feed hydration) surface only when an audio report or user dispatch happens to probe. \n - **Android:** worse. `SnapshotCodec.decodeEnvelope` (`PodcastSnapshot.kt:503-525`) decodes the slim `v` (`rev`/`running`/`schema_version` only — see `nmp_app_podcast_decode_update_frame`, `ffi/snapshot.rs:356+`) directly as `PodcastSnapshot`. Every field is defaulted, so decode **succeeds with an empty library** and `MainActivity.kt:152-157` does `snapshot = next` — every kernel emit **clobbers the UI to an empty state**. This is an active correctness bug, masked only by how rarely frames emit while idle. \n - **Kernel contract gap found:** in `ffi/snapshot_domain_projections.rs`, when a domain rev advances but the builder returns `None` (empty state — library/downloads/identity/widget), `last_emitted` is NOT advanced and no tombstone is emitted. Consequences: (a) a shell consuming sidecars can never learn "downloads cleared / signed out / unsubscribed-all"; (b) an empty domain re-runs `build_podcast_update` (full snapshot build, store lock) **every tick forever**. A small Rust fix (emit `{"rev":N, "<field>":null}` and advance `last_emitted`) is required before shells can rely on sidecars. Also note: each domain builder calls full `build_podcast_update` per changed domain per tick (up to 7 full builds/tick) — acceptable post-#267 (~7.6ms), flag as kernel follow-up, not a blocker. [...] - **Kernel contract gap found:** in `ffi/snapshot_domain_projections.rs`, when a domain rev advances but the builder returns `None` (empty state — library/downloads/identity/widget), `last_emitted` is NOT advanced and no tombstone is emitted. Consequences: (a) a shell consuming sidecars can never learn "downloads cleared / signed out / unsubscribed-all"; (b) an empty domain re-runs `build_podcast_update` (full snapshot build, store lock) **every tick forever**. A small Rust fix (emit `{"rev":N, "<field>":null}` and advance `last_emitted`) is required before shells can rely on sidecars. Also note: each domain builder calls full `build_podcast_update` per changed domain per tick (up to 7 full builds/tick) — acceptable post-#267 (~7.6ms), flag as kernel follow-up, not a blocker. \n  [...]  \n ### Decode change (quoted) \n  \n Before: \n ```swift \n guard let update = Self.decodePodcastUpdate(envelopePayload: data) else { \n     kbLog.error("snapshot frame missing podcast.snapshot projection bytes=\(data.count)") \n     return nil \n } \n ``` \n  \n After: \n ```swift \n guard let domainFrames = PodcastDomainFrames.decode(from: data) else { \n     kbLog.error("snapshot frame missing all podcast.* domain sidecars bytes=\(data.count)") \n     return nil \n } \n ``` \n  \n `KernelUpdateResult` now carries `domainFrames: PodcastDomainFrames` instead of `update: PodcastUpdate`. \n  \n ### KernelDomainFrames.swift — one envelope (confirming NO explicit CodingKeys) \n  \n ```swift \n struct PlaybackDomainFrame: Decodable { \n     var rev: UInt64 = 0 \n     var nowPlaying: PlayerState? \n     var queue: [EpisodeSummary]? \n } \n ``` \n  \n No `CodingKeys` enum. `now_playing` → `nowPlaying` and `queue` via `.convertFromSnakeCase` exactly as the #371 contract requires. \n  \n ### Composite merge + per-domain observable assignment + drop-guard \n  \n `KernelModel` holds: \n - `compositeUpdate: PodcastUpdate` — the merged state from selective domain updates \n - `domainRevTracker: DomainRevTracker` — per-domain last-applied rev for drop-guard \n  \n In `apply(result:)`: \n 1. `mergeDomainFrames(_:into:tracker:)` iterates each present domain, compares `frame.rev > tracker.<domain>`, merges only accepted domains, returns `Bool` (any accepted) \n 2. If accepted: `compositeUpdate.rev = max(domain revs)`, `compositeUpdate.running = true`, then `applyPodcastUpdate(compositeUpdate, fromPull: false)` \n 3. Identity: only updated when `result.identity != .empty` (identity domain was present this frame) — preserves prior `kernelIdentity` when identity didn't change \n  \n ### Tombstone handling [...] Independent review complete. This PR fully removes the empty-library clobber bug and ships the Android per-domain push-consumption half as a faithful twin of the already-approved iOS #403. I read every changed file plus the Rust emitter and the iOS twin for cross-checking. \n  \n ### 1. Clobber removed + cold-start — FULLY FIXED, no blank-library path remains \n - The old `decodeFromJsonElement(PodcastSnapshot.serializer(), v)` path is **gone** — the entire `decodeEnvelope` + `SnapshotEnvelope` block was deleted from `PodcastSnapshot.kt` (diff lines 487–535 removed). The slim `v` is never again decoded as a full snapshot. \n - `MainActivity.kt:166-172` applies `snapshot = merged` **only when `anyAccepted == true`**. A frame with no domains returns `null` from `decodeDomainFrames` (the `if (!frames.hasAnyDomain) null` guard, `DomainFrames.kt`), hits `?: continue`, and never touches state. A frame whose domains are all stale yields `anyAccepted=false` → no assignment. \n - Cold-start hydrator is intact: `MainActivity.kt:140-148` still does the one-shot `bridge.podcastSnapshot()` PULL → `SnapshotCodec.decode` (the full-snapshot decoder, retained). The grid paints on launch. \n - Absent domains are merged via `copy()` touching only present slices — they are never cleared. **The empty-clobber is fully removed, not narrowed.** There is no remaining path where a push frame blanks the library: blanking now requires an explicit library tombstone (`{"rev":N,"library":null}`) at a higher rev, which is the intended all-unsubscribed signal. \n 
c1691-194 | 2026-06-13T00:27:04Z | session:c1691db0-d63e-4062-adad-1cfa0d679d09 |  \n **PR:** https://github.com/pablof7z/podcast-player/pull/407 \n  \n ### Generator approach: hand-rolled emitter (not schemars) \n  \n Chose a **hand-rolled emitter** over schemars for three reasons: \n 1. Schemars would add derive-macro dependencies to the main crate, impacting Android cross-compile times and dep surface \n 2. The Swift files have non-trivial custom decode logic (property wrappers, `decodeIfPresent` with explicit defaults, synthesized memberwise-init preservation via extensions) that schemars schema→Swift can't reproduce without a bespoke transform anyway \n 3. A hand-rolled manifest is explicit and auditable — every field is listed, diffs are readable \n  \n The generator lives in `apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/bin/swift_codegen/` (3 files: `main.rs`, `emit.rs`, `types.rs`). No new crate dependencies. Runnable via `cargo run -p nmp-app-podcast --bin swift-codegen`. \n  \n ### Generated vs NOT YET GENERATED \n  \n | File | Status | \n |---|---| \n | `PodcastAgentContextTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `agent_context.rs`) | \n | `PodcastDownloadTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `download.rs`) | \n | `PodcastLibraryTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `library.rs`) | \n | `PodcastMediaTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `agent.rs`, `voice.rs`, `clips.rs`) | \n | `PodcastSocialTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `social.rs`, `inbox.rs`, `knowledge.rs`) | \n | `PodcastTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (redirect stub) | \n | `PodcastUpdate.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `snapshot_update.rs`, `player/state.rs`) | \n | `PodcastSettingsSnapshot.generated.swift` | ⚠️ NOT YET GENERATED — file is marked with the reason | \n  \n `PodcastSettingsSnapshot` is left hand-maintained because `SettingsSnapshot` uses a mixed `CodingKeys` enum where ~15 fields override to explicit snake_case (`ollama_chat_url`, `stt_provider`, `assembly_ai_*`). The generator field manifest doesn't yet model per-field key overrides. Follow-up tracked in `docs/BACKLOG.md` as `swift-codegen-settings-snapshot`. \n  \n ### Zero-diff faithfulness proof \n  \n ``` \n swift-codegen: writing generated files to .../App/Sources/Bridge/Generated \n   unchanged: PodcastTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastAgentContextTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastDownloadTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastLibraryTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastMediaTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastSocialTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastUpdate.generated.swift \n   skipped:   PodcastSettingsSnapshot.generated.swift (NOT YET GENERATED — see file header) \n swift-codegen: done. \n ``` \n  \n `git diff App/Sources/Bridge/Generated/` shows only the updated header comment on `PodcastSettingsSnapshot`. All 7 generated files are byte-identical. \n 
