c1691-196 | 2026-06-13T00:27:07Z | session:c1691db0-d63e-4062-adad-1cfa0d679d09 | ## D8 fix complete — PR #397 updated, OPEN for re-review \n  \n ### Seam used: self-enqueue (not async-upload, not blocked) \n  \n I found the non-blocking self-dispatch seam: `nmp_app_dispatch_action` only **validates** an action and enqueues an `ActorCommand::DispatchHostOp`, returning immediately — it does NOT round-trip the actor (documented at `tasks_handler.rs:16-23`, and already used by `run_now` and all of `nmp_dispatch.rs`). This is exactly the property the task asked for, so I used the enqueue approach (the preferred option). \n  \n ### New `update_owned` backfill (quoted) \n  \n ```rust \n // Backfill per-episode kind:54 events on a private→public flip by \n // SELF-ENQUEUING one `publish_episode` action per episode (NOT a \n // synchronous loop). Each self-dispatch enqueues an \n // `ActorCommand::DispatchHostOp` and returns immediately, so each episode \n // publishes in its own later actor tick and the actor yields in between — \n // a 50–100 episode flip stays responsive instead of blocking the actor for \n // N sequential Blossom uploads (D8)... \n let episodes_queued = episode_ids_to_backfill.len(); \n let mut episodes_accepted = 0usize; \n for episode_id in episode_ids_to_backfill { \n     let body = serde_json::json!({ "op": "publish_episode", "episode_id": episode_id }); \n     if self_dispatch_publish(handler.app, body) { \n         episodes_accepted += 1; \n     } \n } \n ``` \n  \n New helper `self_dispatch_publish` in `nmp_dispatch.rs` wraps `nmp_app_dispatch_action` for the `podcast.publish` namespace (returns immediately, never blocks). The dispatched `{"op":"publish_episode","episode_id":...}` is the same action the old Swift loop fired via `kernelPublishEpisode` — each lands in its own actor tick. Response carries `episodes_queued` (policy decision, D0-owned) and `episodes_accepted` (FFI accepts). \n  \n ### Preserved \n Flip detection, D0 kernel ownership, show republish, reuse of the `publish_episode` path. `publish_episode` reverted to `fn` (private) since it's reached via dispatch again. Swift side still just triggers `update_owned` (comment updated to note self-enqueue/D8). \n 
