c1691-207 | 2026-06-13T01:29:03Z | session:c1691db0-d63e-4062-adad-1cfa0d679d09 |  \n **PR:** https://github.com/pablof7z/podcast-player/pull/407 \n  \n ### Generator approach: hand-rolled emitter (not schemars) \n  \n Chose a **hand-rolled emitter** over schemars for three reasons: \n 1. Schemars would add derive-macro dependencies to the main crate, impacting Android cross-compile times and dep surface \n 2. The Swift files have non-trivial custom decode logic (property wrappers, `decodeIfPresent` with explicit defaults, synthesized memberwise-init preservation via extensions) that schemars schema→Swift can't reproduce without a bespoke transform anyway \n 3. A hand-rolled manifest is explicit and auditable — every field is listed, diffs are readable \n  \n The generator lives in `apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/bin/swift_codegen/` (3 files: `main.rs`, `emit.rs`, `types.rs`). No new crate dependencies. Runnable via `cargo run -p nmp-app-podcast --bin swift-codegen`. \n  \n ### Generated vs NOT YET GENERATED \n  \n | File | Status | \n |---|---| \n | `PodcastAgentContextTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `agent_context.rs`) | \n | `PodcastDownloadTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `download.rs`) | \n | `PodcastLibraryTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `library.rs`) | \n | `PodcastMediaTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `agent.rs`, `voice.rs`, `clips.rs`) | \n | `PodcastSocialTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `social.rs`, `inbox.rs`, `knowledge.rs`) | \n | `PodcastTypes.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (redirect stub) | \n | `PodcastUpdate.generated.swift` | ✅ Generated (source: `snapshot_update.rs`, `player/state.rs`) | \n | `PodcastSettingsSnapshot.generated.swift` | ⚠️ NOT YET GENERATED — file is marked with the reason | \n  \n `PodcastSettingsSnapshot` is left hand-maintained because `SettingsSnapshot` uses a mixed `CodingKeys` enum where ~15 fields override to explicit snake_case (`ollama_chat_url`, `stt_provider`, `assembly_ai_*`). The generator field manifest doesn't yet model per-field key overrides. Follow-up tracked in `docs/BACKLOG.md` as `swift-codegen-settings-snapshot`. \n  \n ### Zero-diff faithfulness proof \n  \n ``` \n swift-codegen: writing generated files to .../App/Sources/Bridge/Generated \n   unchanged: PodcastTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastAgentContextTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastDownloadTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastLibraryTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastMediaTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastSocialTypes.generated.swift \n   unchanged: PodcastUpdate.generated.swift \n   skipped:   PodcastSettingsSnapshot.generated.swift (NOT YET GENERATED — see file header) \n swift-codegen: done. \n ``` \n  \n `git diff App/Sources/Bridge/Generated/` shows only the updated header comment on `PodcastSettingsSnapshot`. All 7 generated files are byte-identical. \n  \n ### CI drift gate \n  \n New job `swift-bridge-codegen-drift` in `.github/workflows/test.yml` (runs on `ubuntu-latest`, ~10 min timeout): \n 1. `cargo run --bin swift-codegen` \n 2. `git diff --exit-code App/Sources/Bridge/Generated/` — fails with actionable error message if any file drifted \n  \n Coexists cleanly with the existing `android-check` job from #401. \n  [...]  \n ## Summary \n  \n **The settings manifest** — `emit_settings_snapshot()` in `apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/bin/swift_codegen/emit.rs` now emits the full `PodcastSettingsSnapshot.generated.swift`: the 82-field `SettingsSnapshot` struct, the complete explicit `CodingKeys` enum (all ~15 raw snake_case overrides — `ollama_chat_url`, `stt_provider`, the `assembly_ai_*` family, `eleven_labs_*`, `blossom_server_url`, the trailing `nostr_*` block — plus the BYOK `...ByokKeyId`/`...ByokKeyLabel` camelCased-acronym keys), and the custom `decodeIfPresent`-with-defaults `init(from:)` that seeds from `self.init()` and overwrites only present keys, so it can never throw `keyNotFound`. Includes the `decodeCredentialMetadata` / `decodeDate` helpers. `types.rs` carries the `coding_key_override` field + `Field::with_key` builder; `main.rs` dropped the skip + stale NOT-YET-GENERATED docs; the CI drift-gate comment in `test.yml` was de-staled. \n  \n **The wire-compat proof** — three independent confirmations: \n 1. The generated body is **byte-for-byte identical** to the prior hand-maintained body from `import Foundation` onward (verified via `diff`); only the header comment changed. Same field→key mappings, same defaults, same no-throw decode. \n 2. `cargo test -p nmp-app-podcast settings_` → **27 passed**, including the kernel-fixture parity test `settings_fresh_install_matches_fixture`. \n 3. A standalone `swiftc` driver run through the exact `KernelDecoding` decoder config (`.convertFromSnakeCase`) → **all checks passed**: empty `{}` hydrates to the full default with no throw; `effective_stt_provider` + all BYOK credential metadata land via `.convertFromSnakeCase`; the explicit-raw-snake_case keys match verbatim. This matches what the existing `EffectiveSTTProviderDecodeTests` / `SettingsSnapshotParityTests` assert (they pass unchanged). \n  \n **The zero-diff regen** — after committing, re-running the generator reports all eight Generated/ files `unchanged`, and `git diff --exit-code App/Sources/Bridge/Generated` exits 0 (the exact CI drift-gate command). \n  \n **PR URL** — https://github.com/pablof7z/podcast-player/pull/409 (OPEN, left for review). \n  \n One finding worth flagging: the explicit-raw-snake_case `CodingKeys` (e.g. `ollama_chat_url`, `stt_provider`) intentionally do NOT decode under `.convertFromSnakeCase` (the strategy converts the JSON key, then the raw-snake_case CodingKey no longer matches) — they only match a plain/verbatim decoder. This is pre-existing, documented behavior (`EffectiveSTTProviderDecodeTests` notes those fields are unused by the snapshot path), and is preserved byte-identically, not introduced by this change. \n 
