`v.projections[key]` (`apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/ffi/snapshot.rs`, PR #385). So the answer to "does #1068's gate suffice?" is: **it's moot — use typed sidecars with Option-gating; per-domain revs are app-local; zero upstream changes.** \n  \n --- \n  \n ## Item 1 (HEADLINE) — Domain sub-projections as per-domain typed sidecars + per-domain revs \n  \n **What/why:** Replace "one global rev → full-library re-serialize + full-frame decode on any change" with per-domain push deltas. A `PersistPosition` tick (~1/30s) or download-progress report then ships ~1KB of playback/downloads JSON instead of triggering a multi-MB pull+decode. This is the 10x-scale fix the wiki explicitly calls for, and it deletes the four accreted mitigations' root cause. \n **Wiki:** `docs/wiki/change-gate-projections.md` ("Domain Revision Tracking", "Domain Sub-Projections"), `kernel-snapshot-emission.md`, `android-snapshot-push.md`, `reactive-update-model.md`. \n **Scope: L**, staged as 4 independently-landable PRs: \n  \n - **PR-1 (S, ship day 1):** Delete the dead `register_snapshot_projection_gated("podcast.snapshot", …)` block in `apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/ffi/register.rs`. Zero consumer risk (verified above); immediate actor-thread CPU win. Pull path untouched. [...]  \n The per-domain frame work is **not just a perf win — the push pipeline is currently dead on BOTH shells**, and on Android it's actively *harmful*: \n  \n - **iOS:** `KernelBridge.decode(pointer:)` (`App/Sources/Bridge/KernelBridge.swift:234-256`) still requires `v.projections["podcast.snapshot"]`. Since NMP v0.3.0 typed-first the generic projections map is never encoded, and #396 deleted that registration. **Every push frame fails decode** ("snapshot frame missing podcast.snapshot projection") and `sink.handler` never fires. iOS today is 100% pull-driven: report-channel hooks + `pullPodcastSnapshotIfChanged` (full multi-MB Rust serialize + full off-main decode per change). Background rev bumps (triage completion, async feed hydration) surface only when an audio report or user dispatch happens to probe. \n - **Android:** worse. `SnapshotCodec.decodeEnvelope` (`PodcastSnapshot.kt:503-525`) decodes the slim `v` (`rev`/`running`/`schema_version` only — see `nmp_app_podcast_decode_update_frame`, `ffi/snapshot.rs:356+`) directly as `PodcastSnapshot`. Every field is defaulted, so decode **succeeds with an empty library** and `MainActivity.kt:152-157` does `snapshot = next` — every kernel emit **clobbers the UI to an empty state**. This is an active correctness bug, masked only by how rarely frames emit while idle. [...] - **Android:** worse. `SnapshotCodec.decodeEnvelope` (`PodcastSnapshot.kt:503-525`) decodes the slim `v` (`rev`/`running`/`schema_version` only — see `nmp_app_podcast_decode_update_frame`, `ffi/snapshot.rs:356+`) directly as `PodcastSnapshot`. Every field is defaulted, so decode **succeeds with an empty library** and `MainActivity.kt:152-157` does `snapshot = next` — every kernel emit **clobbers the UI to an empty state**. This is an active correctness bug, masked only by how rarely frames emit while idle. \n - **Kernel contract gap found:** in `ffi/snapshot_domain_projections.rs`, when a domain rev advances but the builder returns `None` (empty state — library/downloads/identity/widget), `last_emitted` is NOT advanced and no tombstone is emitted. Consequences: (a) a shell consuming sidecars can never learn "downloads cleared / signed out / unsubscribed-all"; (b) an empty domain re-runs `build_podcast_update` (full snapshot build, store lock) **every tick forever**. A small Rust fix (emit `{"rev":N, "<field>":null}` and advance `last_emitted`) is required before shells can rely on sidecars. Also note: each domain builder calls full `build_podcast_update` per changed domain per tick (up to 7 full builds/tick) — acceptable post-#267 (~7.6ms), flag as kernel follow-up, not a blocker. [...] ### Focus #4 — Drop-guard + composite: PASS \n Per-domain rev-monotonic guard is correct (`frame.rev > tracker[domain]`). All sidecar `rev` fields carry the GLOBAL `update.rev` (not the per-domain counter — the per-domain counter is only the Rust-side emit gate), so the Swift trackers and `lastProcessedRev` live in the same rev namespace; `compositeUpdate.rev = max(domain revs)` correctly clears `applyPodcastUpdate`'s guard. Identity is updated only when its sidecar is present (`apply(result:)` checks `result.identity != .empty`), preserving prior `kernelIdentity` — correct. On `resetAndRestart()` the trackers, composite, and `lastProcessedRev` are all reset together (lines 244-245), so a kernel rev-reset is handled. \n  [...] ANALYSIS: The implementation delivers exactly what was specified with no scaffolding or temporary hacks: \n  \n 1. **Rust kernel owns the projection.** `SocialState.nostr_conversations_snapshot()` is the single source of truth — it groups inbound `AgentNoteSummary` records and `OutboundTurn` entries by `root_event_id`, merges turns in timestamp order, sorts conversations newest-first, and computes `trusted` live against the follow set. The `podcast.social` domain is the 8th delta sidecar registered alongside the existing 7. \n  \n 2. **OutboundTurnCache is durable.** New `src/store/outbound_turn_cache.rs` — bounded ring at MAX=200, dedup by `event_id`, evict-oldest at capacity, atomic tmp-rename write for crash safety. Loaded into `SocialState.outbound_turns` slot on init via `data_dir.rs`. \n  \n 3. **iOS bridge is strictly typed.** `SocialDomainFrame` has no explicit `CodingKeys` (FFI snake_case contract). `nostrConversationFromDTO(_:)` in `KernelModel+DomainMerge.swift` maps the wire `rootEventId` → domain `rootEventID` (uppercase), `Int` timestamps → `Date`, string direction → `Direction` enum. `projectSnapshotDerivedState` applies the kernel slice to `AppState.nostrConversations` when non-empty. Existing `NostrConversationsView` lights up automatically. \n  \n 4. **Android wire is complete.** `SocialDomainFrame`, `NostrConversationDto`, `NostrConversationTurnDto` with `@SerialName` for all snake_case fields. `DomainRevTracker.social` + `mergeFrames` social block. Two new wire tests + schema-constants assertion updated. \n  \n 5. **Golden fixture is stable.** `nostr_conversations` uses `skip_serializing_if = "Vec::is_empty"` so the golden test remains byte-identical. \n  \n RESULTS: 1269 Rust tests pass (0 failures). PR #423 opened against `main`. [...] ## BLOCKER — `domain_revs.social` now has a real production writer \n  \n **Bump idiom adopted:** `Infra::bump()` (state/mod.rs:131) — the canonical reactive-domain mutation idiom. I confirmed by reading the helper that it advances **both** `domain_revs.counter(self.domain)` AND the global signal in one call. The bug was that both mutation sites called the bare `snapshot_signal.bump()` (global-only), leaving `domain_revs.social` frozen at 1. \n  \n **Which domain I mirrored:** every working domain uses `infra.bump()` on a `Domain::X`-scoped `Infra`. I mirrored that exactly — the `SocialState.infra` is already `Domain::Social`-scoped (register.rs:212, mod.rs:422). \n  \n **Inbound** (`agent_note_handler.rs`): added a `Domain::Social`-scoped `Infra` to `AgentNotesObserver` (`with_social_infra`, wired in register.rs from `app_state.social.infra.clone()`). New `bump_social()` calls `infra.bump()` — and I moved it OUTSIDE the cache lock guard to honor the D8 "never bump while holding a Slot guard" discipline the original code violated. \n  \n **Outbound** (`agent_note_responder.rs`): the off-actor task can't hold a full scoped `Infra`, so I threaded `Arc<DomainRevs>` and mirrored the exact two-step `Infra::bump()` performs (`dr.counter(Domain::Social).fetch_add` then `signal.bump()`), in the same order so the social delta is visible on the global-rev frame. \n  \n **Test masking replaced:** the two manual-`fetch_add` social tests are gone. Replaced/added three that drive the REAL observer path: \n - `social_inbound_note_reemits_on_each_new_note_real_path` — the explicit BLOCKER guard: two real inbound notes, asserts the **second** re-emits `podcast.social` (2 conversations in payload). This is the exact line that failed before the fix. \n - `social_empty_emits_tombstone_then_idles` — now drives a real note for the re-emit assertion.
