c1691-224 | 2026-06-13T02:11:48Z | session:c1691db0-d63e-4062-adad-1cfa0d679d09 |  \n The emitter structurally excludes the #371 freeze hazard: it never emits explicit snake_case `CodingKeys` for generated types. All Swift fields are camelCase; `.convertFromSnakeCase` handles the Rust↔Swift key mapping automatically. \n  [...]  \n New job `swift-bridge-codegen-drift` in `.github/workflows/test.yml` (runs on `ubuntu-latest`, ~10 min timeout): \n 1. `cargo run --bin swift-codegen` \n 2. `git diff --exit-code App/Sources/Bridge/Generated/` — fails with actionable error message if any file drifted \n  \n Coexists cleanly with the existing `android-check` job from #401. \n  [...] - Per-key memo is **interior-mutable** (`Mutex<Option<(u64, Value)>>` on each `ProjectionEntry`), because `run(&self)` is driven from `make_update` through a shared `&self` path. This avoids rippling `&mut` through the whole emit path. The closure runs **outside** the memo lock, so a slow/panicking closure never holds it, and `catch_unwind` panic isolation (D6) is preserved for both gated and ungated entries. [...] test result: ok. 19 passed; 0 failed; 0 ignored; 1234 filtered out [...] ## Upstream PR — open ✅ [...] **Fix:** Changed `value_for_tick` to return `Option<serde_json::Value>` (None = closure panicked, key omitted) and wrapped both `(self.f)()` invocations in `catch_unwind(AssertUnwindSafe(|| (self.f)()))`. The outer `run()` was simplified to `if let Some(value) = entry.value_for_tick()`. All 19 snapshot_registry tests passed; 1252 nmp-core tests passed. [...] **crates.io:** Skipped — `cargo publish --dry-run` failed with "all dependencies must have a version requirement" (path deps). Git-rev pin is the delivery mechanism. [...] 2. **Pin bump:** `nmp-{app-template,core,ffi,signer-broker}` bumped `0.2.9` / `104c3f76` → `0.2.10` / `e5070e23`. Also bumped `nmp-feedback` from `3d238e6e` → `2bc722c4` (a one-commit nmp-feedback update I pushed to bump its own NMP pin from `104c3f76` to `e507