c1691-234 | 2026-06-13T02:53:32Z | session:c1691db0-d63e-4062-adad-1cfa0d679d09 | ## Item 2 — Social graph goes reactive + trust gate (`nmp-nip02` adoption) \n  \n **What/why (durable):** Replace `social_handler.rs`'s one-shot, 8s-timeout, hardcoded-`relay.primal.net` pull fetch with the upstream reactive model: construct `FollowListProjection`, register it via `nmp_app_register_snapshot_projection` (the push seam — per established doctrine, no polling), and hydrate kind:0 profiles off the same store. Then wire the trust gate: `ActiveFollowSet` membership → `AgentNoteSummary.trusted` (currently hardcoded `false` in `ffi/projections/social.rs:44`), which is the declared blocker for the agent-to-agent LLM responder port and the conversations approval surface. Keep `fetch_contacts` as a refresh trigger or delete it. \n **Explicitly deferred follow-on (don't bundle):** `nostr-conversations-real-projection` (group `agent_notes` by `root_event_id` into a `NostrConversation`-shaped projection, replacing the Swift compat assembly in `AppStateStore+Nostr.swift`) — depends on the trust gate, lands as its own PR next. \n **Wiki advanced:** `nostr-rust-ffi.md`, `reactive-update-model.md`, `kernel-projections.md`; BACKLOG `social-graph-store-wiring`, unblocks `agent-to-agent-kind1` trust gate. **Not upstream-blocked anymore** — kind:3 store maturity arrived in v0.6.0. \n **Scope:** M. **Files:** `apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/social_handler.rs`, `src/ffi/projections/social.rs`, `src/ffi/register.rs`, `src/ffi/actions/podcast_module.rs`, Cargo (nmp-nip02 dep), Swift: `NostrAgentSurface.swift` / social-tab consumers of `SocialSnapshot.following` (generated DTOs already exist via codegen — drift gate covers them). \n **Validation:** headless `scenarios/social.rs` already exists (nak pre-publish kind:3 → assert snapshot) — extend for reactivity + trusted flag. Sim: sign in → Social tab populates without tapping refresh; a note from a followed pubkey shows trusted. [...] ### 1. THE TRUST-GATE TIMING NUANCE (the crux) — `trusted` is FROZEN-AT-RECEIPT, and that is incorrect \n  \n Definitive answer: **`trusted` is a frozen receipt-time stamp, not re-evaluated at projection.** \n  \n - It is computed once in the kind:1 receipt handler: `agent_note_handler.rs:240-244` — `let trusted = self.follow_set.as_ref().map(|fs| fs.predicate()(&event.author)).unwrap_or(false);` — and baked into the `AgentNoteSummary` written to the cache (`:254`). \n - The projection reads it back verbatim: `state/social.rs:75-81` `agent_notes_snapshot()` just `.clone()`s the cached `Vec<AgentNoteSummary>`; `ffi/snapshot_domain_projections.rs:178` emits `"agent_notes": update.agent_notes` unchanged. No recomputation against the live `ActiveFollowSet` anywhere on the projection path. \n - Worse, the receipt handler dedups by id (`agent_note_handler.rs:258` `if !cache.iter().any(|n| n.id == note.id)`), so a re-delivered kind:1 will NOT refresh the stamp either. A note that arrived `trusted=false` stays false for the life of the process. \n  \n Consequence (exactly the sequence the brief posited): note from X arrives at T1 (X not followed → `trusted=false`) → user follows X at T2 → X's existing note stays `trusted=false` forever (until X authors a brand-new note). The follow set is the source of truth, but notes carry stale trust. For a gate feeding an agent-responder/approval surface, this is the wrong default — it should be live-at-projection. \n  \n Note also the registration-ordering argument (`ActiveFollowSet` before `AgentNotesObserver`, register.rs:309/335) only guarantees correctness for kind:3-then-kind:1 *within the same delivery batch*. It does nothing for the follow-after-note case, which is the common one. If trust were re-evaluated at projection, the ordering wouldn't matter at all — which tells you the ordering is a band-aid over the wrong seam. \n  \n **Minimal fix:** stop stamping `trusted` at receipt. Store the note untrusted/neutral, and compute `trusted` in the social projection builder (`agent_notes_snapshot()` / the snapshot assembly) by applying `ActiveFollowSet::predicate()` to each note's author hex at build time. The `ActiveFollowSet` Arc is already shared and live; the projection just needs a clone of it. That makes follow/unfollow immediately reflect on all existing notes and removes the registration-order dependency. (Keep the npub on the row, but also retain author hex — currently only `author_npub` is stored, so the projection builder would need the hex to feed the predicate; either store `author_hex` on the summary or decode the npub back.) \n  \n ### 2. Reactive population — correct; account-switch reset — INCOMPLETE (gap) \n  \n - Reactive population is correct: `FollowListObserver::on_kernel_event` (social_handler.rs) delegates to upstream `FollowListProjection`, then materializes `SocialSnapshot` into `social_slot` on every kind:3. The scenario empirically proves kind:3 arrives via the standing `account_profile_interest` sub with NO `FetchContacts` dispatch (social.rs reactivity assertion, 20s wait). Upstream confirms `account_profile_interest` = kind:0+3+10002 (nmp-nip02 projection.rs:21; chirp register.rs:377; NmpCore.h:562). No separate subscription needed — confirmed. \n - Account-switch reset is only HALF done. The identity-change hook (register.rs:309-312) calls `active_follow_set.notify_account_changed()`, which resets the follow set and re-seeds self (verified in upstream active_follow_set.rs:223-246). But nothing resets `social_slot` or `agent_notes` on account change: \n   - `social_slot` is a `Slot<_, Session>` (state/social.rs:41) and `Session` = process-lifetime, NOT cleared on switch. So after switching A→B, the Social tab keeps showing **A's `following` list** until B's first kind:3 push arrives (a stale-follows window). The upstream `FollowListProjection::snapshot()` is itself account-correct (keys by live `active_pubkey`), but the app-level `social_slot` is a materialized copy that no one invalidates. \n   - `agent_notes` likewise is never cleared on switch (grep for clear/reset on identity change returns nothing) — so A's notes, carrying A's frozen trust stamps, bleed into B's session. Combined with #1, B could see a note stamped `trusted=true` from A's follow graph. \n  \n **Fix:** in the same identity-change hook, also clear `social_slot` (set to `None`) and `agent_notes` (clear the Vec) so no cross-account state survives a switch. \n  [...] ## Item B — Nostr conversations real projection \n  \n **What/why.** Kernel groups cached kind:1 turns by `root_event_id` (`CachedAgentNote.root_event_id`, `agent_note_handler.rs:76`) into a `NostrConversation`-shaped projection — the canonical domain model already exists in `apps/podcast-agent-core/src/lib.rs` (`NostrConversation`, `NostrConversationTurn`, `ConversationActor`). Requires capturing **outgoing** turns at publish time (`handle_publish_agent_note` knows root + content; today self-authored notes are filtered from the cache). Project per-conversation `trusted` live via the follow set. Then bind the four dead Swift consumers (`NostrConversationsView`, `NostrAgentSurface` badge, `FriendConversationTranscriptView`, `RootView:184` deep-link) to the projection and delete the compat assembly (`AppStateStore+Nostr.swift` `recordNostrTurn`/conversation block, `Domain/NostrConversation.swift` → generated DTO, `AppState.nostrConversations` persistence). Field rides the existing `podcast.misc` domain payload next to `agent_notes` (`snapshot_domain_projections.rs:178`) — no new schema decision needed. Generated Swift DTO via the existing swift-codegen + CI drift gate (#407/#409); **synthesized camelCase keys, no explicit snake_case CodingKeys** (the #371 regression class). \n  \n - **Wiki advanced:** `kernel-projections.md`, `domain-revisions.md`, `nmp-codegen.md`, `agent-friend-delegation.md`, `nostr-social-graph.md`. \n - **Scope:** L. **Heavy Rust + iOS build.** \n - **Files (Rust):** `agent_note_handler.rs` (outgoing-turn capture), `state/social.rs` (`conversations_snapshot`), `ffi/snapshot_update.rs`, `ffi/snapshot_domain_projections.rs` (+tombstone), golden fixture, codegen manifest. **(Swift):** `App/Sources/Bridge/Generated/` (codegen), `KernelDomainFrames.swift`, `KernelModel+DomainMerge.swift`, `AppStateStore+KernelProjection.swift`, the 4 consumer views, `AppStateStore+Nostr.swift`, `Domain/NostrConversation.swift`, `Domain/AppState.swift`. \n - **Haiku-validation:** Rust unit (grouping, ordering by `last_touched`, account-switch clear) + golden-fixture; sim via xcode MCP: build/install, publish a kind:1 to the agent from a second key, observe the conversation appear in Settings → Agent → Conversations and the toolbar badge increment — observable end-to-end behavior. \n - **Independently landable:** yes (projection + binding are valuable even before Item A; A's replies then appear as outgoing turns automatically).
