e. \n  \n ## New regression test \n  \n `apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/ffi/snapshot_domain_queue_identity_tests.rs` — `queue_row_byte_identical_to_full_snapshot_for_content_rich_episode`. Enqueues an episode with an HTML description, chapters, and a transcript, then asserts the slice-local `build_playback_payload` queue equals `serde_json::to_value(build_podcast_update().queue)`. It also sanity-checks the row actually carries description/chapters/transcript and a lowercase id (so a future change that drops fields on *both* paths can't pass silently). Placed in its own file so neither test file exceeds the 500-line limit. \n  [...]  \n - The expensive `build_misc_payload` (full `build_library_snapshot` over all episodes + `all_memory_facts()`) only runs when the **misc domain rev** advances (`snapshot_domain_projections.rs:321` closure is gated on `domain_revs.misc`).  \n - The only sites that advance misc are `wiki` (6 bumps), `knowledge` (3), `picks` (1) — all **low-frequency** (state/wiki.rs, knowledge.rs, picks.rs). \n - The high-frequency "misc" mutators everyone feared — agent-chat streaming, voice, clips, comments — do **not** advance the misc rev. They bump via `signal.bump()` (`snapshot_signal.rs:26`), which touches only the GLOBAL rev, never a domain counter. So their tokens produce a frame where every domain closure sees an unchanged domain rev and returns `None`. No rebuild fires (`Infra::bump` vs `SnapshotUpdateSignal::bump`, mod.rs:131 vs snapshot_signal.rs:26). \n  \n So #425 already killed the hot path. Splitting `podcast.agent`/`wiki`/`clips` out of misc would be **pure server-side hygiene requiring matching iOS+Android frame structs + merge code** (contract-sensitive: snake_case + golden + real-bump gates) for a rebuild that only fires on a manual wiki/pick edit. Not worth a cycle-10 headline. I am **explicitly deprioritizing it.** \n  \n (There is a latent correctness question — does the push frame ever carry agent-chat/voice deltas if they never advanc