rences the deleted symbols** — `BlossomUploader(server:session:)`, the `upload(data:contentType:signer:)` method, `BlossomUploading`. The test target globs `AppTests/Sources/**` (`Project.swift:210`), so this file compiles into `PodcastrTests` → **test target build fails.** The agent's "Swift build passed" was the app target only, not `build-for-testing`. This is precisely the recurring trap. \n  \n **Minimal fix:** delete `AppTests/Sources/BlossomUploaderTests.swift` (its HTTP-transport assertions are obsolete — transport moved to Rust, covered by `nmp-blossom`'s own tests). Optionally also delete the now-dead `KernelSigner` struct + the `BlossomUploadError.invalidResponse` case is already gone. After deletion, re-grep `BlossomUploader|BlossomUploading` across `App/`+`AppTests/` → must be zero. \n  [...] ### Deleted (grep-zero proof) \n  \n **`grep -rn 'KernelSigner\b' App/ AppTests/` = zero** \n  \n From `App/Sources/Services/Nip46/NostrSigner.swift`: \n - `KernelSigner` struct (the only production conformer of `NostrSigner`) \n - `NostrSigner` protocol (now conformer-less) \n - `NostrEventDraft` struct \n  \n The file now contains only `NostrSignerError` (kept — still used by `KernelBridge.swift` + `SignedEventsRegistryTests.swift`). \n  \n ### signEventForReturn chain: REMOVED \n  \n `grep -rn 'signEventForReturn' App/ AppTests/` returns only a dead comment in `KernelModel+BlossomUpload.swift:82` (cleaned up too). \n  \n The chain had exactly two callers: \n - `KernelSigner.sign()` (NostrSigner.swift:86) → `KernelModel.signEventForReturn` → `PodcastHandle.signEventForReturn` \n  \n All three links removed. `SignedEventsRegistry`, `signedEventsRegistry` property, and the underlying `nmp_app_sign_event_for_return` FFI declaration were **kept** (tested by `SignedEventsRegistryTests.swift`; D13 seam remains available). \n  \n ### Build-for-testing result \n  \n **PodcastrTests compiles: YES.** Zero Swift compile errors. The build fails only on the expected linker error: `libnmp_app_podcast.dylib not found — skipping Rust dylib install-name fix` (Rust dylib not built in this worktree). `cargo check -p nmp-app-podcast` finished with no errors. \n  \n ### Three doc fixes \n  \n 1. **BACKLOG `relay-config-c-abi-persistence`**: marked `~~DONE~~`, citing commit `0dcf9680` (PR #220). Load path: `ffi/data_dir.rs:112` (`load_relay_config`); save path: `host_op_handler/settings_actions.rs:391` → `ffi/relay_persist.rs` (`persist_configured_relays`). Also updated the reference in `app-relays-config-ui` entry that said "remains tracked in relay-config-c-abi-persistence" → "is shipped". \n  \n 2. **`apps/nmp-app-podcast/src/ffi/register.rs` comment block**: rewrote the stale "no relay persistence on the C-ABI path / unconditional seed" block. The persistence now exists; the seed is still unconditional for a structural reason (slot is always empty at `register` time — actor reads `initial_relays` only when handling `Start`, which fires after `register` returns), but persisted edits from `data_dir.rs` override it on subsequent launches. \n  \n 3. **BACKLOG `agent-to-agent-kind1` LLM responder loop**: corrected from "still lives on Swift `NostrAgentResponder` path" (stale — class deleted in PR #248) to "Swift `NostrAgentResponder` was deleted in PR #248; kernel re-implementation tracked in `feat/kernel-kind1-auto-responder`". \n  \n 4. **BACKLOG `kernelsigner-deadcode-removal`**: marked `~~DONE~~` (this PR). \n 
